frameDefinitions: An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.
In this frame a Body_mark is present on a Possessor's body.
An Intoxicant is ingested in order to achieve an altered state of consciousness.
This frame deals with a Healer treating and curing an Affliction (the injuries, disease, or pain) of the Patient, sometimes also mentioning the use of a particular Treatment or Medication.
The Invader enters a Land in an aggressive attempt to cripple or dominate its people and its government.
An Agent or Cause causes an Entity to change, either in its category membership or in terms of the value of an Attribute.
frameExamples: Native Americans <t>dyed</t> textiles with dyes made from cedar strips.
Mark has a cancerous <t>mole</t> on his back.
Isis then <t>cured</t> Re by reciting a spell.
In August 1990 ,Iraq was <t>invading</t> Kuwait , which led to the Gulf war .
Our storylines follows the saga outlined by the Ultima Series, but we have <t>modified</t> it in order to make our writing more cohesive.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> is a person who applies the Process to the Material.
The <fen>Alterant</fen> causes a change in the <fen>Material</fen>.
The <fen>Material</fen> is altered by the <fen>Agent</fen> in some useful way.
The point in time or period during which the treatment of the <fen>Material</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Material</fen>s are processed, often a purpose-built facility such as a tannery or water treatment plant.
This role identifies  the <fen>Body_mark</fen>.
This Frame Element denotes the <fen>Possessor</fen> of the <fen>Body_mark</fen>.
The <fen>Intoxicant</fen> is ingested.
The  Healer, anyone who treats or cures the Patient, occurs as the External Argument of verbs:

This   is the sufferer of the injury, disease or pain and can occur as an NP Object in this frame. However, Patient may not be expressed as a separate Frame Element but frequently occurs as the possessor of the Affliction, an example of  role Conflation:  (See section on Conflation.)
The Frame Element Affliction is generally the NP Object of a verb, frequently incorporating the Patient as a possessor, as described above:
The role Treatment is used for treatments and means, distinguished by separate FEs in FN-1.
The injested, applied, injected, etc. substance designed to cure the Patient.
The <fen>Body_part</fen> is the specific area of the <fen>Patient</fen>'s body which is treated.
When the event occurs.
Where the event takes place.
The political area that is being crippled by the <fen>Invader</fen>'s entry.
The army or other self-directed entity that is entering the <fen>Land</fen> in a hostile manner.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Invader</fen> invades <fen>Land</fen>.
This role identifies the location where the <fen>Invader</fen> invades the <fen>Land</fen>.
The sentient entity that effects a change in the <fen>Entity</fen>.
The category of which the <fen>Entity</fen> is a member before the <fen>Agent</fen> causes a change.
The category that the <fen>Entity</fen> belongs to after it has undergone the change.
The value that the <fen>Attribute</fen> assumes as a result of the change that the <fen>Entity</fen> is caused to undergo.
The value that the <fen>Attribute</fen> has before the change takes place.
The abstract or concrete thing or situation that the <fen>Agent</fen> causes to change.
The time at which the change of the <fen>Entity</fen> is caused.
The location where the change of the <fen>Entity</fen> is caused.
